,Recommended,457960,31032882,Posted: 8 April,all,Micah,"I purchased a VR system as a means of avoiding becoming sedentary after I started working from home (at computer all day).  Of all the games I purchased, Holopoint is probably the top for getting my heartrate up.  The first levels are very easy, just introducing you to the game.  Once you hit level 25 though (you can start a play session at any level you have reached in increments of 5) the game is surprisingly fast paced and tiring.When things get intense, I find myself crouched on the ground firing arrows and spinning on my heels like Legolas in LOTR movies.  The game is definitely better with a large play space and I highly encourage some kind of ceiling cable management system to keep the cords from getting tangled around your feet.  This is definitely a Room Scale game.  There is no front/back, the game takes place all around you and above you.My current plan is to add a weighted vest once I am able to beat the game, though I still can't seem to reach level 30."
