,Recommended,457960,23060090,"Posted: 18 May, 2016",all,Pika2,"Game isnotin early accessWhat is Holopoint?Holopoint is a HTC Vive VR game where you shoot blue cubes with a bow and arrow. Seems simple untill they start shooting back. The idea is that you have eyes in the back of yor head so you can both eliminate cubes for points and avoid cubes shooting at you. When a cube dies it more often than not shoots you, when a cube turns orange it shoots you. How do you avoud these shots? You dodge, duck, dip, dive and dodge your way around them. Also there is samurai and ninjas.Is Holopoint good?Holopoint has amassed an impressive 97% positive feedback and with good reason, it is simple but fun. You need no archery skill and it works well even in a relatively small space and for a measly £5 pricetag it is tempting to say no to.For how cheap the game is and for how much fun and exercise you and some friends can get I think that Holopoint is very much worth itIs anything bad?If i'm nitpicking then i'd say that there is no real tutorial and that it was frustrating realising that physical movement is required to progress in this game (which is a lot to ask from a nerd), only other points are perhaps the lack of bow options or any kind of features that would make the game more complex. But I can't really complain for the pricetag."
