,Recommended,457960,25483727,"Posted: 12 September, 2016",all,snoot,"I was skeptical about this game due to other review saying that the bow handling was bad, but with the recent beta changes, all of that is no longer an issue, But there are a number of problems that turn this otherwise fantastic game into a rather frustrating experience. Way moreso than any other game, I frequently find myself getting tangled up in the cables while playing. This is because most of the targets are placed to your sides and often times they are even behind you, so you have to constantly spin around to find a shot and then need to move forward and backwards to dodge. Compare this to something like Space Pirate Trainer where most of the time you fight enemies in front of you and can spend most of your time dodging left to right. Also, There isnt very much in the way of audio queues to tell you where to look, so you constantly need to whip your head around which frequently causes the headset or headphones to shift around. Lastly, the operation of the bow causes me to constatly smack my controllers or headset into eachother, and my efforts to avoid this cause me to misdraw.That said, I only find all of this stuff so frustrating because it gets in the way of my enjoyment of this otherwise fantastic game. And I will continue to put up with it because The thrill of trying to push your way to the next level while your arms start to ache is too satisfying to give up."
